 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'harding', 'comment_id': 763914672.0, 'datetime': '2021-01-20 20:33:23+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "About half of the links removed in this PR point to document on the Bitcoin.org server, not the BitcoinCore.org server.  Is that deliberate?  Bitcoin.org has the strongest claim to being able to host the document as that's where Nakamoto first posted it and (AFAIK) he's never asked for it to be removed from there.

If we remove this from the website out of legal concerns, I think that would imply we'd also need to `git filter-branch` rewrite history to remove the document from the git history.  Otherwise, we're still providing the document in some sense.  I don't have an objection to doing this (carefully, with people prepared to verify that's the only change made, and somebody standing by to fix the website hosting verification script if necessary).

I'd personally prefer to continue hosting the document.  Given that Nakamoto shared everything else he did under his psuedonym, I think we can argue that we're acting in good faith by sharing this document also.  That said, I agree it would be legally safer to remove it, hosting it is not a part of Bitcoin Core's mission, and that there are plenty of other copies available elsewhere for those who want to read it.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
